  "variables": {
    "U": {
      "description": "Utility of accepting the offer",
      "range": {
        "min": "-inf",
        "max": "inf"
      },
      "learnable": false,
      "source": "calculated"
    },
    "alpha": {
      "description": "Utility weight on self's proposed share",
      "range": {
        "min": 0,
        "max": 1,
        "inclusive_min": true,
        "inclusive_max": true
      },
      "learnable": true,
      "source": "learnable"
    },
    "beta": {
      "description": "Utility weight on opponent's proposed share",
      "range": {
        "min": 0,
        "max": 1,
        "inclusive_min": true,
        "inclusive_max": true
      },
      "learnable": true,
      "source": "learnable"
    },
    "delta": {
      "description": "Adjustment factor reflecting the impact of opponent's tokens vs. self tokens",
      "range": {
        "min": 0,
        "max": "inf"
      },
      "learnable": false,
      "source": "data"
    },
    "split_self": {
      "description": "Proposed share for the participant in £",
      "range": {
        "min": 0,
        "max": "inf"
      },
      "learnable": false,
      "source": "data"
    },
    "split_opp": {
      "description": "Proposed share for the opponent in £",
      "range": {
        "min": 0,
        "max": "inf"
      },
      "learnable": false,
      "source": "data"
    },
    "token_self": {
      "description": "Number of tokens found by the participant",
      "range": {
        "min": 0,
        "max": "inf"
      },
      "learnable": false,
      "source": "data"
    },
    "token_opp": {
      "description": "Number of tokens found by the opponent",
      "range": {
        "min": 0,
        "max": "inf"
      },
      "learnable": false,
      "source": "data"
    }
  }
}
</VARIABLES>

<SUMMARY>
A linear utility model capturing the responder's acceptance behavior based on the proposed shares for both self and opponent, modulated by their token contributions. The model uses two learnable parameters (α and β) to calibrate the weights of self and opponent's proposed shares, along with a fixed adjustment factor (δ) to account for the disparity between tokens. The utility is computed to determine acceptance likelihood, with both α and β constrained between [0, 1].
</SUMMARY>

